scene.message:
V.P. Hannya: M-{wait_fr:30}Mayuzumi!!{nl}
What is the meaning of this!?{nl}
Where are we?!{waitkey}Don't tell me...{wait_fr:30} this is{nl}
your doing!{waitkey}{clearbox}You delinquents!{nl}
Trapping us in a place like{nl}
this - what's your aim?!{waitkey}{clearbox}Damn it! Damn it!!{nl}
I don't remember, but I was{nl}
having such a good dream!{waitkey}{clearbox}Ahh! What on earth is{nl}
going on here?! Somebody{nl}
explain!{waitkey}{clearbox}Huff huff huff...{nl}
P-Principal, say something{nl}
to these delinquents too!{waitkey}{ret}

Principal Oishi: Have you{nl}
calmed down, Vice Principal?{nl}
Now then...{wait_fr:30} Mayuzumi,{nl}
everyone,{waitkey}{clearbox}are any of you hurt?{nl}
...{wait_fr:30}...{wait_fr:30}...{wait_fr:30}Good if not.{nl}
By the way, where...{waitkey}{clearbox}are we, I wonder?{nl}
I was having a very{nl}
unpleasant dream...{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: This may be hard for{nl}
you teachers to grasp, but{nl}
in the end, you were saved{waitkey}{clearbox}by us. I won't ask you to{nl}
"thank us," but complaining{nl}
is misplaced as well.{waitkey}{clearbox}I'd appreciate it if you{nl}
kept that in mind.{waitkey}{clearbox}More to the point, teachers,{nl}
do you know anything about{nl}
a "Mirror Shard"?{waitkey}{clearbox}It's important to us.{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: V.P., sir,{nl}
the delinquents are awful!{nl}
"The great me" and my pals,{waitkey}{clearbox}we worked SO hard to save{nl}
the two of{wait_fr:30} y{wait_fr:30}o{wait_fr:30}u!{waitkey}{clearbox}A word of thanks...{wait_fr:30}{nl}
would be nice, y'know.{nl}
Well{wait_fr:30}, whatever{wait_fr:30}, it's fine!{waitkey}It's all in the past!{waitkey}{clearbox}Anyway! Teachers, you know{nl}
of a "Mirror Shard"?{waitkey}{clearbox}"The great me" and my pals{nl}
absolutely need it to become{nl}
the heroes who save{waitkey}{clearbox}the school. It's that item.{nl}
So, you don't know of it?{waitkey}{ret}

V.P. Hannya: "Mirror Shard"???{wait_fr:30}{nl}
Ah, you mean this?{nl}
It was in my suit pocket{waitkey}{clearbox}before I knew it.{nl}
Honestly! Thanks to this,{nl}
the bottom of my pocket tore!{waitkey}{clearbox}My daughter's job-hunting{nl}
this year, and I can't very{nl}
well ask her to mend this...{waitkey}{clearbox}Gefu!{wait_fr:30} Gefufun!!{nl}
Ah...{wait_fr:30} well, none of that{nl}
matters, I suppose.{waitkey}Yep...{wait_fr:30} doesn't matter!!{waitkey}{clearbox}But! What do you brats mean{nl}
to do with a thing like this?!{nl}
No good will come of it.{waitkey}{clearbox}No{wait_fr:30} no{wait_fr:30} no{wait_fr:30} no!{nl}
Hand you a "Mirror Shard" and{nl}
things will only get worse.{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Eeek!!{nl}
What{wait_fr:30} what{wait_fr:30} what{wait_fr:30} what!{nl}
This bald Hannya!!{waitkey}{clearbox}Won't even hear Ayase out{nl}
and just says no!{nl}
So annoying!!{waitkey}{clearbox}That's why YOU, unlike the{nl}
Principal, are hated by all!{waitkey}{clearbox}Just hand over the shard!{nl}
You baldy{wait_fr:30} baldy{wait_fr:30} baldy{wait_fr:30} baldy!{nl}
You jerk! Hand it over!{waitkey}Hand it over!{waitkey}{ret}

Principal Oishi: Now, now,{nl}
Ayase, that won't do.{nl}
A young lady{waitkey}{clearbox}shouldn't use such foul words.{nl}
Vice Principal, before you{nl}
scold the students outright,{waitkey}{clearbox}please first try to see things{nl}
at the same eye level{nl}
as them.{waitkey}{clearbox}Then you'll know at once{nl}
whether a child is lying{nl}
or not.{waitkey}{clearbox}Scolding can come after that.{nl}
Vice Principal, I ask you{nl}
as well.{waitkey}{clearbox}Please give these children{nl}
the "Mirror Shard."{nl}
Children about to do wrong{waitkey}{clearbox}couldn't possibly have{nl}
eyes this honest and{nl}
straightforward.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Hmph. You should have{nl}
just handed it over from{nl}
the start.{waitkey}{clearbox}For right now, we are the{nl}
only ones in this school{nl}
walking the truly right path.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: Sorry. But this is{nl}
important to us - no,{nl}
for saving the school too -{waitkey}{clearbox}a precious thing.{waitkey}{ret}

Principal Oishi: I won't ask{nl}
your reasons now.{nl}
I can tell you're doing{waitkey}{clearbox}what's right, nothing to{nl}
be ashamed of before{nl}
your own pride.{waitkey}{clearbox}But please, no recklessness.{nl}
Don't ever do anything that{nl}
would sadden those who{waitkey}{clearbox}worry about you.{nl}
Now, off you go.{waitkey}{clearbox}Good luck.{waitkey}{ret}

V.P. Hannya: Hmph! I won't{nl}
stop you. Go as you please!{nl}
...{wait_fr:30}...{wait_fr:30}...Hey, you lot!{waitkey}{clearbox}If... if the school goes{nl}
back to normal...{nl}
assemble in the office!{waitkey}{clearbox}I'll lecture you personally.{nl}
And then you'll give me a{nl}
full explanation of all this!{waitkey}{clearbox}Be ready for it!!{nl}
I'll be waiting, together{nl}
with the Principal!{waitkey}{clearbox}Be sure...{wait_fr:30} to come!{nl}
All of you!{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: P...{nl}
Principal...{wait_fr:30} Vice Principal...{waitkey}{clearbox}Heh...{wait_fr:30} leave it to us!{nl}
We'll keep our promise!{nl}
Yeah!{wait_fr:30} "For sure"!{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: There's nothing left{nl}
to do in this room, is there?{nl}
We should hurry on, probably.{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Heh-heh!{nl}
Now the V.P.'ll totally{nl}
think better of us, right!{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Hardly men worthy of{nl}
respect, but our teachers{nl}
all the same.{waitkey}{clearbox}Well, better safe than not.{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Alriiight!{nl}
Now V.P. Hannya owes the{nl}
great me a big one!{waitkey}{clearbox}Kekeke! No more acting{nl}
high and mighty around me!!{waitkey}{clearbox}...{wait_fr:30}...{wait_fr:30}...is what I'd say, but{nl}
I can't... not to Hannya...{nl}
Scary after all... the V.P.!{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: In any case, I'm just{nl}
glad the teachers are{nl}
safe and sound.{waitkey}{ret}

V.P. Hannya: Hmm,{nl}
still, what a good dream...{waitkey}{clearbox}Argh, I can almost remember{nl}
it!! What kind of dream{nl}
was it...?{waitkey}{ret}

Principal Oishi: Still, that{nl}
was an unpleasant dream.{nl}
I'd rather not recall it.{waitkey}{ret}
